  "body": "**Blueprint pin drift: headline relative-Pic nodes carry `\\leanok` but their pins compute the ABSOLUTE Picard group.**\n\nIn `Picard_RelPicFunctor.tex`, three `\\leanok` nodes describe the *relative* functor `T \u21a6 Pic(C\u00d7_kT)/\u03c0_T^*Pic(T)` but pin Lean decls that compute the *absolute* `Pic(C\u00d7_kT)` (iso-class carrier):\n\n- `def:rel_pic_sharp` \u2192 `PicSharp`\n- `lem:rel_pic_sharp_functorial` \u2192 `PicSharp.functorial`\n- `thm:rel_pic_sharp_presheaf` \u2192 `PicSharp.presheaf`\n- (and `def:etale_sheaf` / `etSheaf_group_structure` sheafify the absolute presheaf)\n\nEach node carries a transparent `%`-NOTE flagging the drift, and the honest relative counterparts now exist (`subsec:relpic_relative_functor`: `relPresheaf`, `relFunctorial`, `toRelPresheaf`, all axiom-clean). So this is a **`\\leanok` overclaim**, not a math gap.\n\n**Clean fix is coordinated Lean+blueprint work, not a blueprint-only edit:**\n- Repinning the headline nodes to the relative family needs a `relEtSheaf` built on `relPresheaf` (only `relPresheaf`+`toRelPresheaf` exist; the \u00e9tale-sheaf layer is still on the absolute `presheaf`).\n- Blocked on the \u00e9tale-topology decision (parametrize `J` vs Kleiman \u00a72 `k`-rational-section route) \u2014 same blocker as the FGA `picSharp` rewire.\n\nDo NOT repin piecemeal (def\u2192relative while functorial/presheaf stay absolute) \u2014 that trades one inconsistency for another. See `AJC.picrep` roadmap comment and `I-0060`.",
